==English==

{{rank|sent|keep|myself|273|morning|money|door|round}}

===Etymology===
From [[morn]] + [[-ing]] (refashioned after [[evening]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈmɔ:nɪŋ/}} (''UK'')
*{{audio|en-us-morning.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɔː(r)nɪŋ|-ɔː(r)nɪŋ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{time}}: The part of the [[day]] after [[midnight]] and before [[midday]]: ''one o'clock in the morning'' = 0100 or 1 a.m.
#The part of the day from [[dawn]] to midday.

